The paper deals with a multitask diffusion adaptation problem over networks, which involves multiple agents collaborating to infer multiple parameter vectors. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), networked systems (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT). However, the focus on diffusion algorithms and asynchronous networks suggests that the paper is most likely to be classified under the multi-agent systems category (cs.MA).
